===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|zu|índaba|t=affair, issue, matter; piece of news; story}}, from {{m|zu|ín-|pos=class 9 {{glossary|noun}} {{glossary|prefix}}}} + {{m|zu|-daɓa|pos={{glossary|stem}} meaning ‘affair, matter’}}.<ref>{{R:OED Online|pos=n|id=94180|date=March 2019|nodot=1}}; {{R:Lexico|pos=n}}</ref><ref>{{R:TheFreeDictionary|source=AHD}}</ref>

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ɪnˈdɑːbə/|a=RP}}
* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-indaba.wav|a=Southern England}}
* {{IPA|en|/ɪnˈdɑbə/|a=GA}}
* {{hyphenation|en|in|da|ba}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|South Africa}}
## A [[tribal]] [[conference#Noun|conference]] [[hold#Verb|held]] by [[Nguni]] [[leader]]s.
## {{lb|en|by extension}} Any conference, [[discussion]], or [[meeting#Noun|meeting]].
## ''Chiefly in'' '''one's own''' ''or'' '''someone's indaba''': a [[concern#Noun|concern]], [[matter#Noun|matter]], or [[problem#Noun|problem]]. {{rfex|en}}
# {{lb|en|by extension|Scouting}} An [[international#Adjective|international]] conference of [[Scout]] leaders.

